        				<div class="byline">
					<span class="post_author_intro">By:</span> <span class="post_author"><a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/author/joanne/">Joanne Gallagher</a></span>
					<span class="post_date_intro">Updated:</span> <span class="post_date date_modified" title="2026-01-05">Jan 5, 2026</span>
				</div>
				<div class="post_content">

<p>This is my favorite hummus recipe! With a few simple tricks, you can make the best creamy, smooth homemade hummus that&#8217;s way better than store-bought.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Homemade-Hummus-1200.jpg" alt="Homemade Hummus" class="wp-image-39143" srcset="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Homemade-Hummus-1200.jpg 1200w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Homemade-Hummus-1200-533x800.jpg 533w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Homemade-Hummus-1200-200x300.jpg 200w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Homemade-Hummus-1200-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Homemade-Hummus-1200-683x1024.jpg 683w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>



<p>Hummus is a delicious spread (or dip) made from chickpeas,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/26901/easy-tahini-recipe/" data-type="post" data-id="26901">tahini</a>, lemon, and spices. It is a popular dish in the Middle East and the Mediterranean. You can find it in most grocery stores, but trust me, you&#8217;ll want to skip those and make your own. Homemade hummus is just so much better!</p>



<p>This hummus recipe is a keeper&nbsp;(our family&#8217;s been making it for years!). So many of our readers swear it&#8217;s their forever hummus recipe, too. I&#8217;ve also shared our recipe for&nbsp;<a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/22016/roasted-red-pepper-hummus-recipe/" data-type="post" data-id="22016">roasted red pepper hummus</a>, which I bet you&#8217;ll also love!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Key Ingredients</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Chickpeas (or Garbanzo Beans):</strong> These are the base for hummus, and they can be canned or cooked from scratch. I use both, but homemade chickpeas have a slightly better flavor. Here&#8217;s <a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/26952/how-to-cook-dried-chickpeas/" data-type="post" data-id="26952">how to cook chickpeas</a>.</li>



<li><strong>Tahini:</strong> This sesame seed paste makes it so delicious. You can buy it at the store or make your own. I prefer homemade because it allows me to make my hummus 100% from scratch. Here&#8217;s my&nbsp;<a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/26901/easy-tahini-recipe/" data-type="post" data-id="26901">homemade tahini recipe</a>. To make hummus without tahini, see my tips below the recipe.</li>



<li><strong>Lemon juice:</strong> Skip the bottled stuff! Fresh lemon juice makes all the difference in this recipe.</li>



<li><strong>Garlic:</strong> I use one small clove for just the right amount of flavor, but you can add more for a stronger garlic flavor or use roasted garlic instead. Here&#8217;s&nbsp;<a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/35730/roasted-garlic-recipe/" data-type="post" data-id="35730">how to roast garlic</a>.</li>



<li><strong>Cumin and Salt:</strong> Both improve the flavor of our hummus, and the cumin adds a little extra richness and spice. In our video, I sprinkle Za&#8217;atar seasoning on top for serving, which I love!</li>



<li><strong>Olive Oil:</strong> This guarantees a luxuriously smooth texture. I also like to drizzle a little extra on top when serving. Fruity, light-flavored olive oils are my favorite for making hummus.</li>
</ul>



<p><em>Find the full recipe with measurements below.</em></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to Make Hummus from Scratch</h2>



<p>The secret to the best hummus is all about the order in which you blend your ingredients! Seriously, this simple trick makes a huge difference.</p>



<p><strong>Tip 1: Whip the tahini and lemon juice first.</strong> Add the tahini and lemon juice to your food processor, then, before you add anything else, turn it on and let it run for a minute or two.</p>



<p><em>See the photos&nbsp;below.&nbsp;In the first photo,&nbsp;I&#8217;m pouring tahini into a clean food processor. After a minute of being whirled, whipped, and creamed in the food processor, it turns into the paste you see in the next photo. It&#8217;s lighter in color and much thicker.</em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200.jpg" alt="For the creamiest, smoothest hummus, we add tahini and lemon juice first to our food processor." class="wp-image-39146" srcset="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200.jpg 1200w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200-188x125.jpg 188w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src='data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201200%20800%22%3E%3C/svg%3E' data-src="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200.jpg" alt="For the creamiest, smoothest hummus, we add tahini and lemon juice first to our food processor." class="lazyload wp-image-39146" data-srcset="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200.jpg 1200w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-3-1200-188x125.jpg 188w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200.jpg" alt="Making hummus - Here's what the lemon and tahini looks like after a minute of processing." class="wp-image-39145" srcset="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200.jpg 1200w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200-188x125.jpg 188w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src='data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201200%20800%22%3E%3C/svg%3E' data-src="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200.jpg" alt="Making hummus - Here's what the lemon and tahini looks like after a minute of processing." class="lazyload wp-image-39145" data-srcset="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200.jpg 1200w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-2-1200-188x125.jpg 188w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>



<p><strong>Tip 2: Add the chickpeas in two batches.</strong> Once you have the whipped tahini and lemon, you can add the remaining hummus ingredients. I like adding the chickpeas in two batches, processing the first batch for a minute before adding the rest. Then, I stand back and let my food processor run.</p>



<p><strong>Tip 3: Add a little liquid at the end.</strong> When it looks close to done, I add a splash of cold water while the processor is still running. After a few tablespoons of water, the mixture transforms into&nbsp;fluffy, creamy, whipped hummus.</p>



<p><em>I use cold water, but aquafaba (chickpea liquid) works incredibly well, too. If you want to learn more about it, here&#8217;s our&nbsp;<a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/50401/aquafaba/" data-type="post" data-id="50401">ultimate guide to aquafaba</a>. Some of our readers have also suggested using ice cubes instead of water.</em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200.jpg" alt="What our extra smooth hummus looks like after processing all the ingredients." class="wp-image-39144" srcset="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200.jpg 1200w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200-188x125.jpg 188w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src='data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201200%20800%22%3E%3C/svg%3E' data-src="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200.jpg" alt="What our extra smooth hummus looks like after processing all the ingredients." class="lazyload wp-image-39144" data-srcset="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200.jpg 1200w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1-1200-188x125.jpg 188w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>



<p><strong>Tip 4: Do you need to peel the chickpeas? </strong>I usually skip peeling my chickpeas when making hummus, but it&#8217;s totally up to you! If you have some extra time and want the absolute smoothest texture, go ahead and peel them. It takes about 10 minutes to peel a can of chickpeas, and it does make a subtle difference.</p>



<p><em>The photo below shows slightly smoother hummus made with peeled chickpeas on the left. Even though the peeled chickpeas make a slightly smoother hummus, the difference isn&#8217;t huge. So, if you&#8217;re short on time, skip peeling. Your hummus will still be delicious!</em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200.jpg" alt="A photo showing the comparison of hummus made with peeled chickpeas on the left and skin-on chickpeas on the right." class="wp-image-39147" srcset="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200.jpg 1200w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200-188x125.jpg 188w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" src='data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201200%20800%22%3E%3C/svg%3E' data-src="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200.jpg" alt="A photo showing the comparison of hummus made with peeled chickpeas on the left and skin-on chickpeas on the right." class="lazyload wp-image-39147" data-srcset="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200.jpg 1200w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.inspiredtaste.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/How-to-Make-Smooth-Hummus-1200-188x125.jpg 188w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What to Serve with Hummus</h2>



<p>There are so many delicious ways to enjoy hummus! I love dipping this <a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/46128/no-yeast-flatbread/" data-type="post" data-id="46128">easy fluffy flatbread</a>, <a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/66828/easy-pita-bread/" data-type="post" data-id="66828">homemade pita bread</a>, or fresh, crunchy veggies in it. It&#8217;s also delicious, next to other spreads and dips, like <a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/24825/baba-ganoush-recipe-roasted-eggplant-dip/" data-type="post" data-id="24825">baba ganoush</a> (roasted eggplant dip), <a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/20515/tzatziki-with-feta-cucumber-yogurt-dip/" data-type="post" data-id="20515">tzatziki sauce</a>, <a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/67802/labneh-recipe/" data-type="post" data-id="67802">homemade labneh</a>, and our incredible <a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/27791/tahini-sauce-recipe/" data-type="post" data-id="27791">tahini sauce</a>.</p>



<p>Hummus is also great on sandwiches and wraps, alongside <a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/42640/falafel-recipe/" data-type="post" data-id="42640">homemade falafel</a>, or as a healthy, flavorful filling for <a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/28323/honey-dijon-chicken-lettuce-wraps-with-hummus/" data-type="post" data-id="28323">lettuce wraps</a>. I&#8217;ve even got a recipe for <a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/18404/easy-appetizer-hummus-cups-with-cucumber-and-tomato/" data-type="post" data-id="18404">hummus cups</a> with cucumber and tomato if you want something quick and easy.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">More Recipes with Chickpeas</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/15967/spiced-ground-beef-and-hummus-recipe/" data-type="post" data-id="15967">Hummus with Spiced Ground Beef</a></li>



<li><a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/19298/fresh-chickpea-salad-recipe-with-lemon-and-dill/" data-type="post" data-id="19298">Easy Chickpea Salad</a></li>



<li><a href="https://www.inspiredtaste.net/55819/chickpea-salad-sandwich/" data-type="post" data-id="55819">Smashed Chickpea Salad</a></li>



